defs.docs: Parsers for wavefront's `.obj` and `.mtl` file format for loading meshes.

defs.name: ParseError
defs.docs: A parsing error, with location information.

defs.name: line_number
defs.docs: The line of input the error is on.

defs.name: message
defs.docs: The error message.

defs.name: mtl
defs.docs:
A parser for Wavefront's `.mtl` file format, for storing information about
 the material of which a 3D mesh is composed.

defs.name: MtlSet
defs.docs: A set of materials in one `.mtl` file.

defs.name: Material
defs.value: Material { name, specular_coefficient, color_ambient, color_diffuse, color_specular, color_emissive, optical_density, alpha, illumination, uv_map }
defs.docs:
A single material that can be applied to any face. They are generally
 applied by using the Phong shading model.

defs.name: Illumination
defs.docs: How a given material is supposed to be illuminated.

defs.name: parse
defs.docs:
Parses a wavefront `.mtl` file, returning either the successfully parsed
 file, or an error. Support in this parser for the full file format is
 best-effort and realistically I will only end up supporting the subset
 of the file format which falls under the "shit I see exported from blender"
 category.

defs.name: obj
defs.docs: A parser for Wavefront's `.obj` file format for storing 3D meshes.

defs.name: ObjSet
defs.docs: A set of objects, as listed in an `.obj` file.

defs.name: material_library
defs.docs: Which material library to use.

defs.name: objects
defs.docs: The set of objects.

defs.name: Object
defs.value: Object { name, vertices, tex_vertices, normals, geometry }
defs.docs: A mesh object.

defs.name: name
defs.docs: A human-readable name for this object.

defs.name: vertices
defs.docs:
The set of vertices this object is composed of. These are referenced
 by index in `shapes` contained within each element of `geometry`.

defs.name: tex_vertices
defs.docs:
The set of texture vertices referenced by this object. The actual
 vertices are indexed by the second element in a `VTNIndex`.

defs.name: normals
defs.docs:
The set of normals referenced by this object. This are are referenced
 by the third element in a `VTNIndex`.

defs.name: geometry
defs.docs:
A set of shapes (with materials applied to them) of which this object is
 composed.

defs.name: Geometry
defs.docs: A set of shapes, all using the given material.

defs.name: material_name
defs.docs: A reference to the material to apply to this geometry.

defs.name: shapes
defs.docs: The shapes of which this geometry is composed.

defs.name: Shape
defs.docs: A shape gathers a primitive and groups.

defs.name: primitive
defs.docs: The primitive of the shape.

defs.name: groups
defs.docs:
Associated groups. No associated group means the shape uses the default
 group.

defs.name: smoothing_groups
defs.docs:
Associated smoothing groups. No associated smoothing group means the shape should be rendered
 flat.

defs.name: GroupName
defs.docs: Name of a group.

defs.name: Point
defs.docs: A point specified by its position.

defs.name: Line
defs.docs: A line specified by its endpoints.

defs.name: Triangle
defs.docs: A triangle specified by its three vertices.

defs.name: Primitive
defs.docs: The various primitives supported by this library.

defs.name: Vertex
defs.docs: A single 3-dimensional point on the corner of an object.

defs.name: Normal
defs.docs: A single 3-dimensional normal

defs.name: TVertex
defs.docs: A single 3-dimensional point on a texture. "Texure Vertex".

defs.name: VertexIndex
defs.docs:
An index into the `vertices` array of an object, representing a vertex in
 the mesh. After parsing, this is guaranteed to be a valid index into the
 array, so unchecked indexing may be used.

defs.name: TextureIndex
defs.docs: An index into the `texture vertex` array of an object.

defs.name: NormalIndex
defs.docs: An index into the `normals` array of an object.

defs.name: VTNIndex
defs.docs:
An index into the vertex array, with an optional index into the texture
 array. This is used to define the corners of shapes which may or may not
 be textured.

defs.name: parse
defs.docs:
Parses a wavefront `.obj` file, returning either the successfully parsed
 file, or an error. Support in this parser for the full file format is
 best-effort and realistically I will only end up supporting the subset
 of the file format which falls under the "things I see exported from blender"
 category.
